    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms</strong> to the dish and cook for 1-2 min or until the mushrooms are lightly browned, breaking them up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl and cover with <strong>cling film</strong>, then pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 4 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Add the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>roughly (no need to peel!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms </strong>are browned, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped carrot </strong>to the pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> stout paste</strong>, <strong>Marmite</strong>, <strong>gravy base </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>to the pot with<strong> </strong>350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[460ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>oven baked Fable mushroom & stout casserole</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the casserole has had about 15 min, trim your <strong>green</strong> <strong>beans</strong> and add to a large piece of <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong> (or two!) with a splash of<strong> cold water</strong>, a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and scrunch the foil around the green beans to form a tightly sealed parcel[s], then remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>foil parcel[s] </strong>to the other side of the baking tray[s]</p><p>Firmly crush the <strong>potatoes</strong> with a spatula, add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together, then return the tray[s] to the oven and cook for a final 10-12 min or until the green beans are tender and the potatoes are golden and tender</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-fable-mushroom-and-stout-casserole/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>oven baked Fable mushroom & stout casserole </strong>with the <strong>green beans </strong>and <strong>crushed buttery potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Season to taste</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
